A [[Metric|Metric (mathematics)]] (also referred to as //Distance Function//) on a [[Set]] $$X$$ is a [[Function]]

$$d: X \times X \to [0, \infty)$$

with the following properties:

* $$d(x,y) \geq 0$$
* $$d(x,y) = 0 \iff x=y$$
* $$d(x,y) = d(y,x)$$ ([[Symmetry]])
* $$d(x,y) \leq d(x,z) + d(z,y)$$ (the [[Triangle Inequality]])

[[Metric|Metric (mathematics)]] of a [[Normed Vector Space]] can be //induced// by the [[Norm]].